{
  "texts": [
    "The application of ML will prove essential in the construction of site-specific or location-specific ground-motion prediction models because the situation is more conducive to the flexibility of ML, which can handle various explanatory variables.",
    "Bergen et al. (2019) indicated that ML use in solid earth geoscience can be broadly divided into three categories: automation, modeling (simulation and inversion), and discovery.",
    "For example, phase picking is an example of automation, while ground motion prediction falls under modeling.",
    "The current use of ML in seismology is primarily focused on the automation category.",
    "Applying ML to modeling or discovery may be more difficult; however, we look forward to further research in this area."
  ]
}